The paper discusses methods for improving the performance of data mining models in predictive (supervised) problems by addressing the challenge of missing values in the feature space. This is a common problem in machine learning and data mining, and the paper proposes a novel approach to address it. The paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
